main event: Two flashing objects observed in Kettering, Ohio on October 31, 1962, thought to be satellites.
interesting points: The objects flashed at a rate 4 times faster than a major flashing light,The duration of the observation was 10 minutes,The objects were noted to possibly be satellites or balloons,The observation was made at night, and no sound was reported from the objects,The sighting was documented in Project Blue Book as part of UFO research.
witness description: The witness was likely an individual observer; specific details about the witness were not provided.
